<h1>Configure Shining Sea Sites</h1>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Basic Configuration</h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <p>To start a new site, go to Sites from the navigation menu above and choose "Add new". To edit an existing site, go to Sites and then choose the edit icon next to the site you want to edit.</p>
    <p>Configure the basic attributes of the site:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Name - Seen at the top of each page and in a few places in the text.</li>
    <li>Tagline - A short description of the site; can contain simple HTML if you want to link somewhere.</li>
    <li>Tweet type - A short description of the kind of tweets this site is ranking. For example, "health care industry tweets". This phrase will be used in sentences like, "the top 50 health care industry tweets from February 23, 2014."</li>
    <li>Account type - A short description of the kind of Twitter account this site looks at. For example, "health care industry Twitter accounts". This phrase will also be used in sentences.</li>
    <li>Twitter account username - The username of the Twitter account that is associated with this site, like @GreatHealthTweets. (See "Twitter Tokens" below for the rest of the configuration options for the account.)</li>
    <li>Explanation - A long description of what this site does. Can use basic HTML formatting. See the Great Gov Tweets site for an example.</li>
    <li>CTA iframe - A section of HTML that is included on every page of the site, even older pages with historical data. This is a good spot to put the "Sign up for a 30-day trial" call-to-action.</li>
    <li>MV partner name - If specified, the name of the Measured Voice partner (e.g. Delib) to use when signing people up for a 30-day trial.
    <li>Partner logo URL - (Optional.) The location of an image to use as the logo for the Measured Voice partner.
    <li>Partner link URL - (Optional.) A link to the Measured Voice partner. (If a logo is specified above, it will link here.)
    <li>Google Analytics code - The code used by Google Analytics to identify this site. (Usually something like UA-12345678-10.)</li>
    <li>Active - Check the "active" box when the site is ready to start publishing. Uncheck the "active" box to stop publishing the site.</li>
    <li>Send congrats - Check the "send congrats" box when the site is configured to send congratulatory @reply messages to the top tweets for the day.</li>
    <li>Congrats text - The text of the congratulatory message, like "Congratulations on writing an outstanding health care tweet!" The message can be up to 65 characters long. The date, link, and Twitter account information will automatically be added to the text.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>Before checking the "active" box, make sure the list of accounts, Twitter tokens, host name, and time zone are all properly configured.
