    <h3>Host URL</h3>
    <p>Choose a host name for this site, the URL where the site will be hosted. For example, healthtweets.measuredvoice.com. It should end in measuredvoice.com, with only letters and numbers before the first dot. Make sure that the host name is not already used; type it into a web browser to check.</p>
    <p>Once you've picked the host name, enter it into the "Host URL" box in the site configuration and save the configuration.</p>
    <p>When the site is first published, it will be configured in Amazon Web Services and set up to respond at this host name. If the host name is changed, a new site will be configured at the new hostname but old data won't be copied over automatically.</p>
    
    <h3>Time Zone</h3>
    <p>Enter the time zone this site should use. The time zone affects when the site is published, and what time it considers "yesterday" to have started.</p>
    <p>Common time zones include:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Hawaii</li>
    <li>Alaska</li>
    <li>Pacific Time (US &amp; Canada)</li>
    <li>Mountain Time (US &amp; Canada)</li>
    <li>Central Time (US &amp; Canada)</li>
		<li>Eastern Time (US &amp; Canada)</li>
		<li>London</li>
		<li>Paris</li>
		<li>Sydney</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Be sure to copy the time zone exactly as it appears here.</p>
